\N<Segi>Haah... Haah...
\N<Segi>Haah... Haah...
\N<Yuia>Segi, are you okay? Should we take a break?

\N<Segi>No, I'm fine... If we're caught here, my father and mother's
sacrifices would be in vain...

\N<Yuia>...I see. But let's rest for just a moment. If something
happened to you, I couldn't face Orugi and Seno.
\N<Segi>I'm sorry...
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia... where will we go from here...?

\N<Yuia>Yeah... There is a place we can go to. A place that will
take us in.
\N<Segi>...?
\N<Segi>The underwater ruins city of Miibe...?

\N<Yuia>That's right. It's a bit of a distance from here, but once
we get there, peace should be promised.

\N<Segi>What do you mean by that? If it's alright, could you please
tell me more?

\N<Yuia>...Sure. Actually, my bloodline has had some connections
with that city in the past. We had a bit of an exchange
because of that relationship.

\N<Segi>Wait, please... I understand the situation, but if it's a
city with connections, wouldn't that be even more dangerous?
If Luda and Zuuteruka hear of this...
\N<Yuia>...I think that possibility is slim.

\N<Yuia>Even though I said there were connections between my
bloodline and the underwater ruins city, that was long
before even my great-grandfather's time... Now, no one but
me knows of that connection.
\N<Segi>No one but you, Lord Yuia...?
\N<Yuia>Yes... now that both my father and mother are gone.
\N<Segi>Ah... I'm sorry... I...

\N<Yuia>Haha, maybe I was a bit too harsh. Don't worry, I'm not
bothered by it.

\N<Yuia>My father and mother... Of course, I have no intention of
forgetting them. But the truth is, being bound by that won't
allow me to live looking forward.
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia...

\N<Yuia>Besides... it's not just me who's suffering. You're the
same, aren't you?

\N<Yuia>Right now, the only one in front of my eyes is you. And in
your eyes too, only my figure is reflected.

\N<Yuia>We only see each other... It might be lonely, but surely
it's not unfortunate. Rather... I'm even grateful for this
fortune.
\N<Yuia>Segi, I'm thankful that your life was saved...

\N<Yuia>My father and mother... and your parents Orugi and Seno.
Protected by various people, we are still alive today. I'm
grateful to be living this moment with you.
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia... I... I also feel the same way... I'm happy.

\N<Yuia>Haha... That's good. If even you rejected me, I would truly
have nowhere to go.
\N<Segi>Such a thing... I could never reject you, Lord Yuia...

\N<Yuia>...Segi, let's live strongly. To the point where we can
laugh off things like Luda as minor stumbles.

\N<Yuia>And if that's difficult... at least let's rely on each
other, trust each other, and support each other as we live.
\N<Yuia>Even if death separates us, still...
\N<Segi>...Yes.
\N<Yuia>...Hmm?
\N<Segi>L-Lord Yuia... does that mean... could it be...
\N<Yuia>Yes. That's what I mean. Was I being too roundabout?
\N<Yuia>Segi... I want you to live with me.
